  ],
  "description": "Zarr is a format for chunked, compressed, N-dimensional arrays commonly used in scientific computing and big data. A Zarr store is a directory (or ZIP archive) containing JSON metadata files and binary chunk data. The .zarray JSON file describes an array: shape (list of dimension sizes), chunks (chunk shape), dtype (NumPy dtype string e.g. '<f4'), compressor (Blosc, gzip, bz2, lzma, zstd, or null), fill_value, order ('C' row-major or 'F' column-major), and filters. .zattrs contains arbitrary user-defined metadata. Groups use .zgroup JSON marker. Chunk files are named by coordinates (e.g., '0.0.0' for a 3D array). Zarr v2: .zarray per array; Zarr v3: zarr.json at root. Used in: xarray, Dask, Pangeo geospatial stack, neuroimaging (NeuroZarr), Zarr-based OME-NGFF microscopy. Detection from file content only.",
  "category": "Science",
  "author": "WPFHexaEditor Team",
  "preferredEditor": "text-editor",
  "references": {
    "specifications": [
      "Zarr Storage Specification v2 — zarr.readthedocs.io/en/stable/spec/v2.html",
      "Zarr Storage Specification v3 — zarr-specs.readthedocs.io/",
      "OME-NGFF Specification — ngff.openmicroscopy.org"
    ],
    "WebLinks": [
      "https://zarr.readthedocs.io/",
      "https://zarr-specs.readthedocs.io/",
      "https://github.com/zarr-developers/zarr-python",
      "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zarr_(format)"
    ]
  },
