  "aiHints": {
    "analysisContext": "Zarr store structure: directory tree where each array has a .zarray JSON file describing: zarr_format (2 or 3), shape, chunks, dtype, compressor ({id:'blosc',cname:'lz4',...} or null), fill_value, order ('C'/'F'), filters. Chunk files are named '0', '0.1', '0.0.0' etc. (.zgroup marks a group node, .zattrs holds user attributes). Zarr v3 replaces .zarray with zarr.json. Binary chunk files can be compressed Blosc blocks with Blosc header: magic 0x02010200.",
    "suggestedInspections": [
      "Verify .zarray or .zgroup file starts with '{' (0x7B)",
      "Parse zarr_format field: 2 for Zarr v2, 3 for Zarr v3",
      "Read 'shape' array to understand array dimensions",
      "Read 'chunks' array to understand chunking strategy",
      "Check 'compressor' field: null=uncompressed, or {id:'blosc'/'gzip'/'zstd'} for compression"
    ]
  },
